  "prompt": "Why is HBO drama The Newsroom being canceled after the third season?",
  "response": "\"The Newsroom,\" created by Aaron Sorkin, concluded after its third season primarily due to a combination of factors including declining viewership, mixed critical reception for the later seasons, and Sorkin's own desire to move on to new projects. HBO confirmed the show's cancellation in 2014, stating that the third season would be its last. Sorkin mentioned in interviews that he felt the series had run its course and that he was ready to focus on other creative endeavors. Despite having a strong start and passionate fans, the decision reflected HBO's shift in focus to developing new series that aligned with its evolving programming strategy.",
